Q6.1: In replication/synchronization case, we use the Linked Data Event Stream (LDES) approach to model and communicate data updates on a given KG. However, there is no standard approach to model KG changes (despite the existence of some vocabularies that can deal with it such as Activity Streams 2), much less ontology/schema changes that may impact a whole (mirrored) KG. This is often treated as an after thought, specially when the ontology definition process didn't consider change modelling and communication.   I think it would be beneficial to include a these kind of considerations within the ontology creation methodology.
